---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;

const likertScale = [
  { label: 'Strongly agree', value: 5 },
  { label: 'agree', value: 4 },
  { label: 'Neutral', value: 3 },
  { label: 'disagree', value: 2 },
  { label: 'Strongly disagree', value: 1 },
];

const fruityBlissItems = [
  { code: 'B1', text: 'The likelihood that FruityBliss fruit juice would be a delicious drink is very high.' },
  { code: 'B3', text: 'The likely standard of FruityBliss fruit juice is extremely high.' },
  { code: 'B4', text: 'FruityBliss fruit juice appears to be of good quality.' },
  { code: 'B5', text: 'My image of FruityBliss fruit juice is good.' },
  { code: 'B6', text: 'I view the FruityBliss brand name positively.' },
];

const proFrizItems = [
  { code: 'E1', text: 'The ProFriz Frisbee Challenge appears to be an event of superior status.' },
  { code: 'E3', text: 'The likelihood that the ProFriz Frisbee Challenge would be an event worth watching is very high.' },
  { code: 'E4', text: 'My image of the ProFriz Frisbee Challenge is that it is a highly enjoyable event.' },
  { code: 'E5', text: 'One could believe that the ProFriz Frisbee challenge has high entertainment value.' },
  { code: 'E6', text: 'The likely standard of the ProFriz Frisbee Challenge event is extremely high.' },
];
---

<BaseLayout title="Quant" description="Quantitative methods — secondary and primary data, measurement, and analysis">
  <div class="quant-layout">
    <nav class="quant-toc" aria-label="On this page">
      <h2 class="quant-toc-title">On this page</h2>
      <ol class="quant-toc-list">
        <li><a href="#intro">Introduction</a></li>
        <li>
          <a href="#secondary-data">Secondary data</a>
          <ol>
            <li><a href="#data-sources">Data sources</a></li>
            <li><a href="#secondary-analysis">Data analysis</a></li>
          </ol>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="#primary-data">Primary data</a>
          <ol>
            <li><a href="#method">Method</a></li>
            <li>
              <a href="#questionnaire">Questionnaire</a>
              <ol>
                <li><a href="#questionnaire-example-1">Example 1: Semantic differential</a></li>
                <li><a href="#questionnaire-example-4">Example 4: Likert scale</a></li>
              </ol>
            </li>
            <li><a href="#sampling">Sampling</a></li>
            <li><a href="#primary-analysis">Data analysis</a></li>
          </ol>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <article class="quant-article">
      <p class="back-link"><a href={`${base}methods/`}>← Methods</a></p>
      <h1 id="intro">Quant</h1>
      <p class="quant-lead">
        Numerical data: secondary sources (readily available) and primary collection (surveys, experiments,
        observation). Your research objective dictates whether you need numbers, words, or both.
      </p>

      <section id="secondary-data" class="quant-section">
        <h2>Secondary data</h2>
        <p>
          The getting data is short (easier), the using data part is long and hard. Secondary data is readily available
          to analyze. F.e. you can copy columns from Worldbank. The data context refers to the country and a time frame.
        </p>

        <section id="data-sources" class="quant-subsection">
          <h3>Data sources</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Public domain data</strong>: easy for ethical clearance. You have to specify and name it.</li>
            <li><strong>Private data</strong>: f.e. Bloomberg</li>
            <li><strong>Company data</strong>: requires NDA.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Whatever data you collect, you have to argue <strong>WHY</strong> this data and not other data. You need a
            reference for it. Every decision you make must come with a reference.
          </p>
          <p>
            Then you must <strong>operationalise the data</strong>: to match theory with variables. There may be
            different variables for the same construct. There will be multiple variables for 1 thing: which one do you
            pick? Must be informed from literature.
          </p>
          <p>
            You must create a table with columns <strong>&ldquo;variable&rdquo;</strong>, <strong>&ldquo;dataset&rdquo;</strong>{' '}
            and <strong>&ldquo;operationalised (variable in the dataset)&rdquo;</strong>. Examples of variables column
            are Y, X, c (constants, covariants, &hellip;). The dataset column could contain the URL to the dataset. One
            example row could be &ldquo;poverty&rdquo;, &ldquo;url&rdquo; and &ldquo;gini coefficient&rdquo;.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="secondary-analysis" class="quant-subsection">
          <h3>Data analysis</h3>
          <p>
            This is the hard part for secondary data. They call it <strong>model specification</strong>. Ideally put into
            some formula: y = a + bx + c.
          </p>
          <p>
            This will be something new from my thesis. Not done before. But parts of it will be done before. A good theory
            is always summarized in a math formula.
          </p>
          <p>Needs a minimum of 40 rows.</p>
        </section>
      </section>

      <section id="primary-data" class="quant-section">
        <h2>Primary data</h2>
        <p>
          Numerical data. Long on the getting the data part. Shorter on the using of the data. Dataset with numbers only.
        </p>

        <section id="method" class="quant-subsection">
          <h3>Method</h3>
          <p><strong>Techniques:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Survey</strong>. Survey always uses questionnaire measurement</li>
            <li><strong>Experiment</strong>: P/P (pre vs post), quasi and PF</li>
            <li>
              <strong>Observation</strong>: for example eye tracker, scanner. Could be machine observation, structured,
              counting how many (camera).
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="questionnaire" class="quant-subsection">
          <h3>Questionnaire</h3>
          <p>Questionnaire. NOT always survey.</p>

          <section id="questionnaire-example-1" class="quant-example">
            <h4>Questionnaire example (1)</h4>
            <p class="quant-example-type">Semantic differential scale</p>
            <div class="quant-questionnaire">
              <div class="quant-questionnaire-meta">
                <span>Questionnaire nr</span>
                <span class="quant-questionnaire-boxes" aria-hidden="true">
                  <span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span>
                </span>
                <span class="quant-questionnaire-range">[1&ndash;3]</span>
              </div>
              <p class="quant-questionnaire-title">
                Telephone survey: Brand equity of provincial, national and regional rugby teams of South Africa
              </p>
              <p class="quant-questionnaire-say">
                <strong>Say:</strong> Hello, my name is &hellip;. I am phoning on behalf of a student doing research on
                rugby in South Africa. May I please ask you a few questions, it will only take a few minutes?
              </p>
              <p class="quant-questionnaire-screen">
                Are you interested in rugby? (If respondent says NO, say thank you and goodbye. If YES proceed.)
              </p>
              <div class="quant-semantic-scale">
                <p class="quant-semantic-question">
                  <strong>Q1</strong> On a scale of 1 to 5, where 1 is not a supporter at all, and 5 is an extreme
                  supporter, to what extent are you a rugby supporter?
                </p>
                <div class="quant-semantic-track" role="group" aria-label="Rugby supporter scale 1 to 5">
                  <span class="quant-semantic-anchor">Not at all</span>
                  <div class="quant-semantic-options">
                    {[1, 2, 3, 4, 5].map((n) => (
                      <span class="quant-semantic-option">
                        <span class="quant-semantic-num">{n}</span>
                      </span>
                    ))}
                  </div>
                  <span class="quant-semantic-anchor">Extreme supporter</span>
                  <span class="quant-semantic-entry" aria-label="Recorded response">4</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="questionnaire-example-4" class="quant-example">
            <h4>Questionnaire example (4)</h4>
            <p class="quant-questionnaire-say quant-questionnaire-say--standalone">
              <strong>SAY:</strong> Looking at this poster, please indicate to what extent you agree OR disagree with each
              of the statements; where 5 means you strongly agree and 1 means you strongly disagree. Please circle the
              respondent&rsquo;s answer.
            </p>
            <div class="quant-table-wrap">
              <table class="quant-likert-table">
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th scope="col"></th>
                    <th scope="col">Statement</th>
                    {likertScale.map((col) => (
                      <th scope="col" class="quant-likert-col">
                        {col.label}
                        <span class="quant-likert-value">({col.value})</span>
                      </th>
                    ))}
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr class="quant-likert-intro">
                    <td colspan="7">
                      <strong>SAY:</strong> Supposing you drink fruit juice:
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  {fruityBlissItems.map((item) => (
                    <tr>
                      <th scope="row">{item.code}</th>
                      <td>{item.text}</td>
                      {likertScale.map(() => (
                        <td class="quant-likert-cell" aria-hidden="true">○</td>
                      ))}
                    </tr>
                  ))}
                  <tr class="quant-likert-intro">
                    <td colspan="7">
                      <strong>SAY:</strong> Supposing you enjoy sport:
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  {proFrizItems.map((item) => (
                    <tr>
                      <th scope="row">{item.code}</th>
                      <td>{item.text}</td>
                      {likertScale.map(() => (
                        <td class="quant-likert-cell" aria-hidden="true">○</td>
                      ))}
                    </tr>
                  ))}
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
          </section>
        </section>

        <section id="sampling" class="quant-subsection">
          <h3>Sampling</h3>
          <p>Target population. No one gives you the population. You need to define this yourself.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="primary-analysis" class="quant-subsection">
          <h3>Data analysis</h3>
          <p>Descriptive or inferential (conceptual model testing).</p>
          <p>
            For 1 construct, you need at least <strong>5 items</strong>. 5 questions to measure 1 thing. Question items.
            For latent variables. For those 5 questions, you need a reference. You need to find the items in literature.
            This becomes a master doc of items which will be an annex to the PhD. Could be 20 pages of items. The mother
            doc. Mostly deal with latent variables. F.e. motivation. Every X and Y needs at least 5 items. Start finding
            them already now. Don&rsquo;t come up with your own questions.
          </p>
          <p>
            For every item questions, you need at least <strong>5 people</strong>. The final questionnaire can not be
            longer than <strong>3 pages</strong> or <strong>7 to 10 minutes</strong>. You need references for all X and Y.
          </p>
        </section>
      </section>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style is:global>
  html {
    scroll-behavior: smooth;
    scroll-padding-top: 6rem;
  }
</style>

<style>
  .back-link {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .back-link a {
    color: var(--color-maroon);
  }

  .quant-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: start;
    max-width: 1100px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .quant-layout {
      grid-template-columns: min(250px, 27%) 1fr;
    }
  }

  .quant-toc {
    position: sticky;
    top: 5.5rem;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-maroon);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
    max-height: calc(100vh - 6rem);
    overflow-y: auto;
  }

  .quant-toc-title {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    margin: 0 0 0.65rem 0;
  }

  .quant-toc-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .quant-toc-list > li {
    margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
  }

  .quant-toc-list ol {
    margin: 0.35rem 0 0.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    list-style: none;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .quant-toc-list ol li {
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .quant-toc a {
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .quant-toc a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .quant-article {
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .quant-article h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.45rem, 3vw, 1.85rem);
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    scroll-margin-top: 5.5rem;
  }

  .quant-lead {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .quant-section {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    scroll-margin-top: 5.5rem;
  }

  .quant-section > h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    line-height: 1.3;
    scroll-margin-top: 5.5rem;
  }

  .quant-subsection {
    margin-top: 1.75rem;
    scroll-margin-top: 5.5rem;
  }

  .quant-subsection > h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
    scroll-margin-top: 5.5rem;
  }

  .quant-example {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    scroll-margin-top: 5.5rem;
  }

  .quant-example > h4 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    margin: 0 0 0.35rem 0;
  }

  .quant-example-type {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
  }

  .quant-section p,
  .quant-subsection p,
  .quant-example p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .quant-section ul,
  .quant-subsection ul {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .quant-section li,
  .quant-subsection li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .quant-questionnaire {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: #fafafa;
    max-width: 100%;
  }

  .quant-questionnaire-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
  }

  .quant-questionnaire-boxes {
    display: inline-flex;
    gap: 0.25rem;
  }

  .quant-questionnaire-boxes span {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 1.25rem;
    height: 1.25rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    background: #fff;
  }

  .quant-questionnaire-range {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
  }

  .quant-questionnaire-title {
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.95rem !important;
    margin-bottom: 1rem !important;
    max-width: none !important;
  }

  .quant-questionnaire-say {
    font-size: 0.9rem !important;
    max-width: none !important;
  }

  .quant-questionnaire-say--standalone {
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem !important;
  }

  .quant-questionnaire-screen {
    font-size: 0.9rem !important;
    font-style: italic;
    max-width: none !important;
  }

  .quant-semantic-scale {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .quant-semantic-question {
    font-size: 0.9rem !important;
    max-width: none !important;
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem !important;
  }

  .quant-semantic-track {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
  }

  .quant-semantic-anchor {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    min-width: 5.5rem;
  }

  .quant-semantic-options {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  .quant-semantic-option {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 2rem;
    height: 2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    background: #fff;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .quant-semantic-num {
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .quant-semantic-entry {
    margin-left: auto;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 2rem;
    height: 2rem;
    border: 2px solid var(--color-maroon);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-maroon);
  }

  .quant-table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    max-width: 100%;
  }

  .quant-likert-table {
    width: 100%;
    min-width: 40rem;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .quant-likert-table th,
  .quant-likert-table td {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 0.55rem 0.6rem;
    text-align: left;
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  .quant-likert-table thead th {
    background: rgba(113, 32, 56, 0.08);
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
  }

  .quant-likert-table thead th:first-child,
  .quant-likert-table thead th:nth-child(2) {
    text-align: left;
  }

  .quant-likert-col {
    min-width: 4.5rem;
  }

  .quant-likert-value {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
  }

  .quant-likert-table tbody th {
    background: rgba(113, 32, 56, 0.05);
    font-weight: 600;
    white-space: nowrap;
    width: 2.5rem;
  }

  .quant-likert-intro td {
    background: rgba(113, 32, 56, 0.04);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .quant-likert-cell {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
</style>
